<h1 id="installation">Installation</h1>

<p>Use your distribution’s package manager, examples:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">emerge weechat <span class="c"># Gentoo, Funtoo, ...</span>
<span class="nb">sudo </span>apt <span class="nb">install </span>weechat <span class="c"># Debian, Ubuntu, Mint, ...</span>
<span class="nb">sudo </span>pacman <span class="nt">-S</span> weechat <span class="c"># Arch, Manjaro, ...</span>
<span class="nb">sudo </span>dnf <span class="nb">install </span>weechat <span class="c"># Red Hat, CentOS, Fedora, ...</span></code></pre></figure>

<blockquote>
  <p>WeeChat is also available for: OpenBSD, NetBSD, FreeBSD, GNU Hurd, macOS, Solaris and more.</p>
</blockquote>

